had it all sunshine
and fucking roses.

86
00:09:02.964 --> 00:09:05.033
He had nothing.
He had no choice.

87
00:09:05.133 --> 00:09:07.601
You don't just get handed
anything in life.

88
00:09:07.701 --> 00:09:09.170
You got to work for it.

89
00:09:09.270 --> 00:09:12.941
Got to be better. do better.

90
00:09:13.707 --> 00:09:16.544
School can help you learn.
Carter.

91
00:09:16.644 --> 00:09:18.479
Is it the only way? No.

92
00:09:18.579 --> 00:09:21.816
But when you're given a chance
to make your life better.

93
00:09:21.950 --> 00:09:23.985
you fucking grab it.

94
00:09:27.822 --> 00:09:30.458
Carter. I want you happy.

95
00:09:31.259 --> 00:09:33.660
But I need you ready.

96
00:09:33.661 --> 00:09:37.832
Ready for the hard parts when
they come. and they're coming.

97
00:09:41.102 --> 00:09:43.803
I already had two parents die.

98
00:09:43.804 --> 00:09:45.306
I figured that out.

99
00:09:46.841 --> 00:09:49.010
You're right.

100
00:09:49.777 --> 00:09:51.512
But I'm not sure
that's something

101
00:09:51.612 --> 00:09:54.682
you ever figure out. Carter.

102
00:09:56.050 --> 00:09:59.487
And I'm sorry every day
that that happened to you.

103
00:10:10.498 --> 00:10:15.168
My dream is to cowboy.

104
00:10:15.169 --> 00:10:19.373
To be like Rip. like your dad.

105
00:10:31.319 --> 00:10:33.354
Then you go to work.

106
00:10:36.124 --> 00:10:37.458
Today.

107
00:10:38.726 --> 00:10:42.062
Rip will take you
to the 10-Petal.

108
00:10:42.063 --> 00:10:45.900
Cowboys don't get a day off
'cause they're hungover.

109
00:10:50.804 --> 00:10:54.542
Better hurry up and get dressed.
He won't wait for ya.

110
00:10:56.877 --> 00:10:58.046
Yes. ma'am.

111
