They. uh. they did
an angioplasty.

114
00:11:36.517 --> 00:11:37.918
Will she live?

115
00:11:38.019 --> 00:11:39.520
She'll be fine.

116
00:11:40.854 --> 00:11:43.123
When can she come home?

117
00:11:43.124 --> 00:11:45.826
Your grandmother's already tried
to escape twice. baby girl.

118
00:11:45.926 --> 00:11:47.795
She's a tough one.

119
00:11:47.928 --> 00:11:49.630
Can I see her?

120
00:11:49.730 --> 00:11:52.266
No. she wants
to talk to us first.

121
00:12:04.912 --> 00:12:07.481
She's gonna be okay. Oreana.

122
00:12:14.955 --> 00:12:20.028
Kino. I need you to make peace
with your brother.

123
00:12:21.295 --> 00:12:22.896
You lied to me.

124
00:12:23.731 --> 00:12:26.133
No. I-I changed my mind.

125
00:12:26.134 --> 00:12:27.601
I need you to fall in line.

126
00:12:27.701 --> 00:12:29.837
That's the best trick he knows.

127
00:12:29.970 --> 00:12:31.304
And make no mistake.

128
00:12:31.305 --> 00:12:33.841
you need him a lot more
than he needs you.

129
00:12:33.941 --> 00:12:35.843
Well. he's the one
who needs to find a new job.

130
00:12:35.976 --> 00:12:37.478
Oh. stop it.

131
00:12:37.611 --> 00:12:41.181
You're a fine cowboy.
but you're not a true cattleman.

132
00:12:41.182 --> 00:12:42.483
not like Rip Wheeler.

133
00:12:42.583 --> 00:12:44.518
And you got

134
00:12:44.618 --> 00:12:46.186
a fine head for business. but...

135
00:12:46.187 --> 00:12:48.356
you don't have
Beth's killer instinct.

136
00:12:48.489 --> 00:12:49.690
Well. they're gone. too.

137
00:12:49.823 --> 00:12:53.661
Robert William. you...

138
00:12:53.761 --> 00:12:56.029
...you are so goddamned weak.

139
00:12:56.030 --> 00:12:58.198
That's why I'm leaving
the ranch to you.

140
00:12:58.199 --> 00:13:01.334
It's not your prize.
it's your protection.

141
00:13:01.335 --> 00:13:03.170
And Beth and Rip?

142
00:13:03.171 --> 00:13:05.073
They're assets.

143
00:13:05.173 --> 00:13:09.410
so y'all don't end up in here
or somewhere far worse.

144
00:13:13.481 --> 00:13:14.815
You're my sons.

145
00:13:14.915 --> 00:13:17.251
and you're linked at the hip...

146
00:13:18.319 --> 00:13:21.721
...whether you like it or not.
from cradle to grave.

147
00:13:21.722 --> 00:13:23.557
I'll fetch my shovel.

148
00:13:24.425 --> 00:13:26.227
- Enough.
- Is that all.

149
00:13:26.327 --> 00:13:28.028
Mother?

150
00:13:28.162 --> 00:13:33.067
No. It's fucking everything.

151
00:13:34.302 --> 00:13:36.104
Hmm.

152
00:13:40.374 --> 00:13:41.975
Rest up.

153
00:14:03.697 --> 00:14:05.099
First time I cowboyed
with my old man.

154
00:14:05.199 --> 00:14:07.568
I was sore for a week.

155
00:14:07.701 --> 00:14:09.270
Shoot.

156
00:14:09.403 --> 00:14:11.939
Father and son
cowboying side by side.

157
00:14:12.072 --> 00:14:13.741
that's damn beautiful. <i>viejo.</i>

158
00:14:13.841 --> 00:14:15.876
Mm-hmm.

159
00:14:19.680 --> 00:14:21.815
Can't wait to do it with my kid.

160
00:14:21.915 --> 00:14:24.117
Yeah. well.
don't fucking rush. Azul.

161
00:14:24.118 --> 00:14:25.953
Too fucking late.

162
00:14:27.421 --> 00:14:28.456
What's that?

163
00:14:28.589 --> 00:14:30.624
Delilah just found out.

164
00:14:30.724 --> 00:14:33.261
I mean. well.
we-we just found out.

165
00:14:33.394 --> 00:14:34.695
Congratulations.

166
00:14:34.795 --> 00:14:36.130
Thanks. boss.

167
00:14:36.264 --> 00:14:37.298
Whoa. Rip.

168
00:14:37.431 --> 00:14:38.932
You got to pull over.

169
00:14:39.032 --> 00:14:40.768
No. no. no. no. don't you
fucking throw up in my truck.

170
00:14:40.901 --> 00:14:42.303
Hold on a second.

171
00:14:48.376 --> 00:14:50.144
Oh. kid's gonna be hating life.

172
00:14:50.278 --> 00:14:51.945
He already does. Look at him.

173
00:14:52.079 --> 00:14:54.448
- Let's go. <i>borrachín.</i>
- What's that one mean?

174
00:14:54.548 --> 00:14:55.949
- What's that mean. now?
- Like a boozehound.

175
00:14:57.117 --> 00:14:58.318
Come on. now.

176
00:14:58.319 --> 00:15:00.954
Let's go. son. Let's go!

177
00:15:01.054 --> 00:15:03.991
<i>Vámonos.</i>

178
00:15:04.992 --> 00:15:06.860
- Come on. now.
- Oh. shit.

179
00:15:06.960 --> 00:15:08.729
Watch out.

180
00:15:08.829 --> 00:15:10.264
You get it out of you?

181
00:15:10.364 --> 00:15:12.600
- Let's go.
<i>- Agárrate.</i>

182
00:15:14.335 --> 00:15:15.703
Get in. boy.

183
00:15:23.411 --> 00:15:25.279
Right in here.

184
00:15:31.352 --> 00:15:33.187
Hi.

185
00:15:36.790 --> 00:15:38.858
Is Carter okay?

186
00:15:38.859 --> 00:15:40.228
He's better now.

187
00:15:42.996 --> 00:15:44.665
Oreana.

188
00:15:45.499 --> 00:15:48.001
Will you help me find
something sweet to eat?

189
00:15:48.135 --> 00:15:50.904
Please.

190
00:15:51.705 --> 00:15:54.875
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

191
00:15:55.676 --> 00:15:57.945
- See you later.
- Thanks.

192
00:16:02.115 --> 00:16:04.117
Ah.

193
00:16:04.952 --> 00:16:06.686
Should've bought you whiskey.

194
00:16:10.190 --> 00:16:11.992
I'm sorry.

195
00:16:12.092 --> 00:16:15.796
Oh. I've raised boys.

196
00:16:16.530 --> 00:16:18.832
Hell. I'm still raising 'em.

197
00:16:19.867 --> 00:16:21.200
If the worst he's done to date

198
00:16:21.201 --> 00:16:23.404
is a little drunken
hell-raising.

199
00:16:23.504 --> 00:16:25.406
you've done all right by him.

200
00:16:29.310 --> 00:16:31.077
Feels like we're apologizing

201
00:16:31.078 --> 00:16:33.046
for our children
our entire lives.

202
00:16:33.146 --> 00:16:36.817
Maybe we're just apologizing
for ourselves.

203
00:16:36.917 --> 00:16:38.686
Hmm.

204
00:16:40.153 --> 00:16:43.023
Your retirement. Beulah...

205
00:16:44.825 --> 00:16:46.527
...was unexpected.

206
00:16:46.627 --> 00:16:49.096
Yeah. Impulsive maybe.

207
00:16:49.229 --> 00:16:50.598
Little bit.

208
00:16:52.700 --> 00:16:54.067
You know. it changes things.

209
00:16:54.167 --> 00:16:55.936
I don't see how.

210
00:16:56.704 --> 00:16:59.573
10-Petal's stronger
with you and Rip.

211
00:16:59.673 --> 00:17:00.908
whether I'm there or not.

212
00:17:01.041 --> 00:17:04.244
Well. I didn't agree
to work with your son.

213
00:17:04.378 --> 00:17:06.279
I agreed to work with you.

214
00:17:06.280 --> 00:17:09.282
Well. I'm not
leaving tomorrow. so...

215
00:17:09.283 --> 00:17:12.219
if you're willing.
I'd love for you to just

216
00:17:12.320 --> 00:17:13.787
take it a day at a time.

217
00:17:14.622 --> 00:17:18.626
Well. we'll talk about it when
you're out of here. shall we?

218
00:17:19.827 --> 00:17:21.762
You just get better.

219
00:17:24.432 --> 00:17:26.600
But he is a mistake.

220
00:17:27.868 --> 00:17:30.438
He's a liability. Beulah.

221
00:17:30.538 --> 00:17:32.472
He's my son. Beth.

222
00:17:32.473 --> 00:17:37.077
I will not apologize for him
or myself.

223
00:18:10.844 --> 00:18:12.880
If you love her.
trust she'll come around.

224
00:18:12.980 --> 00:18:15.015
H-How do I know
if she'll come around. though?

225
00:18:15.115 --> 00:18:17.951
You don't.
That's the trust part.

226
00:18:18.051 --> 00:18:19.687
Should I saddle up a longhorn?

227
00:18:20.454 --> 00:18:22.689
Boy's learned
his whiskey limits.

228
00:18:22.690 --> 00:18:24.324
Do me a favor.
Grab a couple of these guys

229
00:18:24.425 --> 00:18:26.025
and clear them hog traps.

230
00:18:26.026 --> 00:18:27.860
The rest of you guys
are with Azul and I.

231
00:18:27.861 --> 00:18:30.998
- Let's go to work.
- Austin. Miguel.

232
00:19:12.272 --> 00:19:14.373
You know the rule
around here. right?

233
00:19:14.374 --> 00:19:17.043
Puke. you got to lick it up.

234
00:19:17.044 --> 00:19:20.247
- You hear that. <i>güero?</i>
- Shut the fuck up.

235
00:19:22.683 --> 00:19:24.117
You good?

236
00:19:24.918 --> 00:19:26.887
Yeah. I'm fine. sir.

237
00:19:26.987 --> 00:19:29.423
Get it together. Carter.
Come on. now.

238
00:19:31.224 --> 00:19:32.960
Daylight's burning.

239
00:19:59.252 --> 00:20:00.821
Any good?

240
00:20:02.255 --> 00:20:03.824
It's great.

241
00:20:05.593 --> 00:20:08.461
Read it half a dozen times.

242
00:20:08.462 --> 00:20:11.765
I'll never understand
reading a book over again.

243
00:20:11.865 --> 00:20:13.266
You already know the ending.

244
00:20:13.400 --> 00:20:16.937
Well. sometimes knowing
the ending's the best part.

245
00:20:19.072 --> 00:20:20.641
Mm.

246
00:20:31.785 --> 00:20:33.987
I know that look. McKinney.

247
00:20:34.087 --> 00:20:37.491
Why choose Rob-Will?

248
00:20:37.591 --> 00:20:41.261
Why wear your wedding ring?

249
00:20:42.830 --> 00:20:44.832
Because I'm still married.

250
00:20:44.965 --> 00:20:46.333
- Yeah.
- I mean. not that I want

251
00:20:46.466 --> 00:20:49.469
to be with her.
if that's what you're asking.

252
00:20:50.804 --> 00:20:52.105
Well...

253
00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:56.243
...sometimes the important thing
is to choose.

254
00:21:01.549 --> 00:21:05.385
Kino may be my son.
but he's not my flesh and blood.

255
00:21:06.319 --> 00:21:08.321
Not like Rob-Will.

256
00:21:08.455 --> 00:21:11.391
I love him. I do.

257
00:21:12.259 --> 00:21:13.627
But...

258
00:21:16.930 --> 00:21:20.267
...Rob-Will's the choice
I felt I had to make.

259
00:21:20.367 --> 00:21:23.503
Yeah. and how about when he runs
your ranch into the ground?

260
00:21:23.604 --> 00:21:27.206
I don't know that I have it
in me to care anymore.

261
00:21:27.207 --> 00:21:29.008
- No?
- No.

262
00:21:29.009 --> 00:21:30.878
I'm tired. Everett.

263
00:21:32.012 --> 00:21:34.682
I'm so fucking tired.

264
00:21:36.717 --> 00:21:40.020
I just want to get on
with the getting on.

265
00:21:42.289 --> 00:21:45.158
